It’s a detective game that starts out a little weird but quickly becomes very interesting. On the surface it seems like a visual novel, but it has quite a lot of gameplay as well... Things to do. Take it from me, who was bored to tears with Steins Gate, because it was JUST hours of reading; This is way more compelling and all voice lines have some quality VO as well. ..

『エムジェイ 1992年3月号』

1992年2月15日発売
表紙は「機動戦士ガンダム0083 STARDUST MEMORY」より「ガトー専用ゲルググ」と「ガンダム試作2号機」です。巻頭特集は8ページにわたって「ゲルググ・バリエーション」になっており、「シーマ専用ゲルググFs」を中心に作例が組まれてます。
また、プラモデルでの新シリーズとして「シルエットフォーミュラー」の告知がされたのも今号でありました。

2枚目

昨日(9/27)、遂に発売となりましたニンテンドースイッチ用ソフト「ドラゴンクエストXI 過ぎ去りし時を求めて S」。3DS版をクリアはしていたのですが、PS4版は未プレイの為に購入しました。ボイスドラマ付きの「ゴージャス版」を購入したのですが、ボイスドラマ台本や電子メモパッド付きの「夢のゴージャス」版が存在していたんですね・・・不覚でした(ToT)
暫くは睡眠不足の日々が始まります。

3〜4枚目 「全日本模型ホビーショー」にてガンプラのマスターグレードシリーズの新作が発表されましたね！
「FAZZ Ver.Ka」が遂に来ました！！しかもプレバンではなく一般販売です。
しかし定価が・・・原作のように3機揃えようとしたら、確実に財布が大変な事になりますね。
まぁ、発売に辿り着いた事に感謝なんでしょうね〜
記 : 2019年9月28日

caption.text:
Coming in at the last minute with this one. 
This was fully intended to be an underwater theme of some sort but ended up coming out like Dark Souls meets Donkey Kong Country? Either way I leant into that with a B minor to C minor movement for the B section. I was very tempted to keep the whole piece modulating up by a semitone every time it went between sections but that was far too silly.

Otherwise it's mostly an E minor to D major vamp that I wholeheartedly lifted from The Doors (the intro is also really stolen) but hey, everyone borrows ideas right?

caption.text: I just finished Link’s Awakening for the Switch, and I’m still smiling! 😃 What a brilliant, and masterful remake of a 26 year old classic.  I never played the original back in 93 on the Gameboy, but I know it’s always been considered one of the best Zelda games to date.  So I was going in fresh, and boy did I have a blast!  This game is a prime example of how consistent Nintendo is, and how well their games age.  Except for the obvious visual overhaul (which is out of this world cute) and a few quality of life improvements, it’s identical to it’s older brother…and it holds up incredibly well.  It’s a reminder of just how meticulously crafted this game is.  If you’re a fan of Zelda games, especially the older ones…you owe it to yourself to check this one out. | #nintendoswitch #nintendo #zelda #linksawakening

caption.text:
EA e Respawn Entertainment revelaram um novo trailer de Star Wars JEDI: Fallen Order. O vídeo mostra elementos de jogabilidade, partes do enredo e novos personagens.
Chamado de “Missão do Cal”, o vídeo explica que Cal Kestis está procurando por algo na Galáxia que também é de interesse do Império e de outras pessoas. Na jornada, ele encontra alguns aliados e inimigos poderosos, claro.
Star Wars JEDI: Fallen Order chega dia 15 de novembro de 2019 para PlayStation 4, Xbox One e PC.

Episode 17 of Absent Minded Podcast is live! Link in bio.⁣
.
We've got one double stuffed episode for you all this week. The news is thick, since we recorded two days later than usual so that we could talk all about PlayStation's third State of Play showcase that streamed on Tuesday, September 24th. The big dog of this one? A new The Last of Us Part II trailer and a release date, but that was just the icing on an otherwise very satisfying cake. But it's not all news, oh no! Travis decided to dust off the ol' Nintendo Switch and brings us a review of The Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening remake as well as early impressions of Fire Emblem: Three Houses. Sure, he's late to class on that one, but we won't hold it against him. Ethan tosses out some hot takes on the new Star Wars: Jedi Outcast port on PS4 and even throws Star Wars: Battlefront 2 a bone. And Drew... well, Drew's just pretty.
.

COMO RECORRER KILOMETROS RAPIDO Y FACIL SIN MOVERSE (y totalmente legal)
1_Hay que asegurarse de tener la sincroaventura activada para poder realizar esto (esto se hace con google fit)
2_Luego hay que instalar Defit (link:https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.fitness.debugger)
3_Al entrar debemos poner las configuraciones tal cual yo las tengo y conectarlo a la misma cuenta de gmail que pokemon go y google fit
Y listo, dejamos cerrado pokemon go y en 15 minutos entramos a ver como suman esos km (ya lo probe por un tiempo y no hay riesgo de ban. Anoche hice 64km mientras dormia)

caption.text:
So I must say, upon initial reaction to the ending of Tag, my reaction in my previous post still holds truth. However.
-
-
After lots of reading, listening to radios, and watching YouTube videos, I can not say Tag is a bad map. Its truthfully brilliant once you give it some thought, and delivers a tragic ending no one saw coming.
-
-
I will however, say that Tag is still a disappointing map to what they were building up. All we heard about since origins was “The Great War”. All through Blops4, it seemed to be the main point of focus leading up to Tag, giving most of us the impression we would be participating. Like I had hoped.
-
-
Instead, we were completely thrown for a loop. Given something we just did not expect. So now this beckons the question, was this a bad thing? I dont think so. I actually think on Treyarch’s end, if their resources were as limited as its been rumored, was pretty brilliant. Because they pulled it off.
-
-
Its a beautiful map. A nice reimagination of Call of the Dead, which really was one of my favorite maps ever. The radios are super interesting, the wonder weapons are pretty decent and easy to get, and it really plays like old school zombies. -
-
The ending makes sense too. Given all things considered and understanding their ultimate sacrifice, it is actually really beautiful. Its sad. It actually does make you think once you’re given more context. Once you understand, there was no way to end the cycle with all them existing. It didnt matter how they changed the future, their existence as a whole was the fracture that threw the very universe into chaos. -
-
Now i ask you, what do you think? I want to know your opinions, feel free to drop a comment or DM me personally. -
-

caption.text:
For quite awhile now, the Assassin’s Creed series has been Ubisoft’s most successful when it comes to the number of copies sold. As of the company’s most recent update, that’s not something that has changed, either, with the total copies sold growing even larger.
.
In a tweet shared by industry analyst Daniel Ahmad, Ubisoft recently updated their sales figures for all of their major franchises. Assassin’s Creed still sits stop the rest and has sold a staggering 140 million copies across all entries that have made up the series. As of this year, the Assassin’s Creed series is 12 years old meaning that on average, over 11.5 million copies of any title in the series have been sold each year. That’s pretty crazy. Ubisoft went on to say that of that total, 95+ million are unique players.
.
The next closest franchise to Assassin’s Creed is that of Just Dance. However, even though it’s in second Just Dance still only has approximately half the lifetime sales that AC does having sold 70 million copies total. According to Ubisoft’s stats, over 2.5 billion songs have been played in Just Dance games to date.
.

caption.text: So here's my poor post for the #shmupsareshooters Just found a photo I had taken and it looks as dire as the experience was.  I must have taken this photo when i had just got the Switch recently. I had been testing out Tate mode as I had logged into my Nintendo account and downloaded a previous purchase of Gunbird (from when I originally had a switch)  The game feels floaty as hell and plenty lag, even more so with the 8bitdo stick. Plenty Gameover screens were seen, well maybe one or two before I had enough.  Top it of with all the annoyance of trying to sync the thing in the first place it's back in its box and put out of sight. The games intro and demo scenes were good to watch at least. #gunbird #nintendoswitch #8bitdo #ninstagram #retrogaming #videogamers  #oldschoolgaming #retrogamers #gamesconsoles #retrocollectiveeurope #instagamers #nintendo #shooters #shootemups #shmupsareshooters
